    <!-- Help Texts -->
    <string name="help_add_name_title"><b>Name and Description</b></string>
    <string name="help_add_name">This page contains basic information about the activity.\n\nName: (Required) Enter a short descriptive name for the activity.\n\nDescription: In a paragraph or two describe how to carry out the activity. You can also type or paste links into this box.</string>
    <string name="help_add_people_title">People and Age</string>
    <string name="help_add_people">This page contains information relating to people.\n\nNumber of People: Enter a the minimum and maximum number of people that can perform this activity at the same time.\n\nAge: Some activities aren\'t appropriate for younger persons. If the activity requires persons to be the age of majority select "Adult". Otherwise choose "All Ages" or "Kids Only".</string>
    <string name="help_add_time_title">Time and Duration</string>
    <string name="help_add_time">This page contains time related information.\n\nDuration: Enter the minimum and maximum amount of time the activity will take. For example watching a tv show might take 30 minutes.\n\nTime: Enter the time of day during which the activity can be performed. For example certain activities can only be done at night.</string>
    <string name="help_add_environment_title">Environment and Cost</string>
    <string name="help_add_environment">This page contains information related to the activity\'s environment.\n\nEnvironment: Specify whether the activity is indoor, outdoor or around the town (e.g going to a bar downtown). Activities could potentially have more than one environment.\n\nCost: Estimate how much the activity will cost. Also specify whether the cost is total for the whole group or if it is per person.</string>
    <string name="help_add_location_title">Location</string>
    <string name="help_add_location">This page is only relevant if the activity is specific to a geographical location. If the activity does not depend on a location, skip this step.\n\nEnter the location via one of three different methods:\n1) Current Location: Uses your current position as the location.\n\n2) Use Map: Find the location of the activity on the map, press the map to set a marker at that location, then push the "Use Selected" button.\n\n3) Enter Address: Enter the address of the activity into the dialog box. The location will be automatically calculated.</string>
    <string name="help_add_tags_title">Tags</string>
    <string name="help_add_tags">This page contains tags which are descriptive words about the activity. Tags allow us to provide more accurate recommendations.\n\nActivities must have at least one tags associated with them.\n\nSome tags may be automatically generated based on the activity\'s name and description. You can also add tags manually as well by clicking the "Add Tags Manually" button.</string>
    
